==Geography==
[[Image:Jubilee.JPG|thumb|right|[[Walney Bridge]] and [[Walney]] viewed from Barrow]]

Barrow-in-Furness is situated at the tip of the [[Furness]] [[peninsula]] on the north-western edge of [[Morecambe Bay]]. The town centre and major industrial areas sit on a fairly flat coastal shelf, with a gentle incline leading away from the coast. Ten miles (16&nbsp;km) to the north-east is the southern boundary of the English [[Lake District]].

