=== Islands ===
{{Main|Islands of Furness}}
The town is sheltered from the Irish Sea by [[Walney Island]], a <span style="white-space:nowrap">14&nbsp;mile&nbsp;(22.5&nbsp;km)</span> long island connected to the mainland by the [[Bascule bridge|bascule]] type [[Walney Bridge|Jubilee bridge]]. About 13,000 live on the isle's various settlements, mostly in [[Vickerstown]], which was built to house workers in the rapidly expanding shipyard. Another significant island which lay in the Walney Channel was [[Barrow Island (England)|Barrow Island]], but following the filling of the channel to create land for the yard it is now directly connected to the town. Other islands which lie close to Barrow are [[Piel Island]], whose castle protected the harbour from marauding [[Scot]]s, [[Sheep Island (England)|Sheep Island]], [[Roa Island]] and [[Foulney Island]].

